I don't know if, Ryan, you want to answer this one, or?

00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:38.320
Sure.

00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:39.320
Yeah.

00:05:39.320 --> 00:05:44.279
So I'm assuming, like, hosting them internally, you just mean, like, hosting them on a web

00:05:44.279 --> 00:05:46.640
server that you control.

00:05:46.640 --> 00:05:51.799
I think there's a really substantial difference, which is in terms of compliance and security

00:05:51.799 --> 00:05:54.500
and getting those things approved.

00:05:54.500 --> 00:06:00.140
So when you're, I've kind of worked in data sciences in a pretty highly regulated environment.

00:06:00.140 --> 00:06:04.179
And I think most of the time, when you're trying to spin up a new web server, a new

00:06:04.179 --> 00:06:07.980
web service, an API, or something like that, there's a lot of work you need to do to make

00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:11.420
sure that that thing is secure and compliant, and that everybody at your company agrees

00:06:11.420 --> 00:06:14.579
with you that it's secure and compliant and necessary.

00:06:14.579 --> 00:06:19.220
And that can take months and months and months to get off the ground.

00:06:19.220 --> 00:06:23.500
And so the thing I love about Posit Connect, both when I was a user of it before I joined

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:27.779
Posit, and now as a kind of worker, somebody who works here, is that it gives you basically

00:06:27.779 --> 00:06:31.500
like a pre-approved space for deploying all of these different things.

00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:36.100
So that makes it better, both because, you know, you can do things faster, but it also

00:06:36.100 --> 00:06:40.260
makes it a lot more secure, because it means that if there is a security change at your

00:06:40.260 --> 00:06:44.859
organization, like you're switching identity providers, or you're going from password to

00:06:44.859 --> 00:06:49.339
SAML or something like that, that happens in one place, as opposed to having 100 different

00:06:49.339 --> 00:06:50.700
web applications that you're hosting.

00:06:50.700 --> 00:06:51.859
So it really simplifies things.

00:06:51.859 --> 00:06:56.579
And I think with data science, and these types of sort of rapid prototyping experiences,

00:06:56.579 --> 00:07:01.179
it's really a great tool for that, because it puts it all in one secure box.

